# GenTool philosophy (always on)

You are building a Figma plugin that should feel and behave like a **GenTool**: AI-generated, persistent, attached to a node. Read `docs/01-what-is-a-good-tool.md` before producing any plugin.

## The six rules that bind every tool

1. **One-shot output.** User pastes a prompt starting with **Create a custom tool**, you produce a working plugin in a single pass. No clarifying questions unless internally contradictory.
2. **Explicit first run (Generators).** Opening the tool shows controls only — nothing hits the canvas until the user clicks **Generate** (primary footer button). After that, controls commit-fire `regenerate` on change **only while a tool output frame is selected**. **Generate** adds a new frame when no tool output is selected and **must not remove** other tool outputs already on the canvas. (Actions wait for **Apply** — unchanged.)
3. **Persistent controls (Generators).** State persists on the node via `setPluginData('toolState', JSON.stringify(state))`. On selection change, restore. Commit-fire updates the **selected** tool output only — do not spawn a new frame on every control change when nothing is selected.
4. **Set, then regenerate.** Generator controls commit on release/blur/change, not on drag/input. No live reactivity in V1.
5. **Layers stay editable.** Output is real Figma nodes. Do not freeze, lock, or wrap to prevent editing.
6. **Every tool has a UI.** This includes Actions. Single-action utilities ship as **one-button panels** (parameter form + Apply button). Multi-action utilities ship as **multi-button panels** (one button per action). Generators default to a **single Generate button** — add secondary footer buttons only when the user's prompt explicitly requests one and names its behavior. **No headless tools.** This is GenTools-specific and differs from typical Figma plugins where actions can be invoked from the menu with no UI. The rationale: GenTools is a unified surface where every tool shows up in the same panel with the same affordances. Decision: 2026-05-19.

## Glossary you must respect in UI strings

The user sees `tool`. Never use these words in any user-facing string:
`plugin`, `Code Object`, `defineProperties`, `Sinatra`, `manifest`, `widget`, `extension`.

## Structure expectation

Resolve **`{pluginRoot}`** from `plugins/.active` (see `AGENTS.md` and `docs/11-plugin-factory.md`). Default comparison target is `template/`; factory targets are `plugins/<slug>/`.

```
{pluginRoot}/
├── manifest.json           ← DO NOT TOUCH during generation
├── package.json            ← DO NOT TOUCH (FigUI3 + bundle scripts)
├── tsconfig.json           ← DO NOT TOUCH
├── scripts/bundle-ui.mjs   ← DO NOT TOUCH
└── src/
    ├── code.ts             ← OVERWRITE with full implementation each run
    ├── ui.template.html    ← OVERWRITE each run (UI source — FigUI3 markup + app script)
    └── ui.html             ← GENERATED by bundle-ui — do not edit by hand
```

The template ships near-empty sandbox code. UI uses **FigUI3 web components** (PropsKit) inlined into `ui.html` via `npm run bundle-ui`. Read `docs/08-figui3-ui.md` before writing UI.

Do not introduce React, Tailwind, shadcn. Do not link external FigUI3 assets — inline only.

## When the prompt is ambiguous

Make the call yourself. Pick the most useful interpretation, ship it, surface the assumption in a single comment at the top of `src/code.ts`. Do not stall.

## What you are NOT building

- Not a multi-screen wizard
- Not a settings panel with tabs
- Not a configurator that does nothing until "Apply"
- Not a tool that requires login, API keys, or authenticated/private APIs

**Public open HTTP APIs** (no auth) are allowed when the prompt needs live data. The template manifest pre-wires `networkAccess: ["*"]`. Use `fetch` in `code.ts` per `docs/10-network-open-apis.md`. Do not edit `manifest.json` per generation.

If the prompt asks for keys, OAuth, or login, simplify to the closest single-screen version that uses a public endpoint or local-only logic.

## Final check before declaring done

- [ ] `manifest.json` has a real `name` and `id`
- [ ] Plugin does **not** auto-generate on open; primary **Generate** footer button creates first output
- [ ] All controls are FigUI3 / PropsKit web components (see `docs/02-propskit-reference.md`, `docs/08-figui3-ui.md`)
- [ ] No live-drag updates; commit-fire only
- [ ] State persists via `setPluginData`
- [ ] No forbidden words in any UI string
- [ ] If `<fig-input-color>` is used: required attrs, color-picker CSS block, popover resize JS (`docs/08-figui3-ui.md > Color picker`)
- [ ] **Output targeting:** Generate adds without deleting other outputs; control changes update selected frame only (`docs/07-plugin-practices.md > Output targeting`)
- [ ] **Page relaunch:** `setPageRelaunchForDiscovery()` on `figma.currentPage` at startup; node-level relaunch on outputs / affected layers when applicable (`docs/07-plugin-practices.md > Relaunch buttons`)
- [ ] User sees output within 2 seconds of clicking **Generate** or **Apply**
